{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"ab927159-c0b5-4e57-9ce4-3f2505887189","content":"The issue is clear: F# requires files to be listed in dependency order in the `.fsproj`. `Services.fs` depends on `Domain.fs`, but `Services.fs` is listed first. Let me fix the ordering.","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_RRti6jDtjBURShvMuzNBrz","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-103276939f5b4de299ee665aa0e6afc1/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj","old_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>","new_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-103276939f5b4de299ee665aa0e6afc1/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj."}],"interactionId":"b52bba34-ea57-49a8-8775-d90d066895ad","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The issue is clear. In F#, file order matters — files can only reference types/modules defined in files listed *before* them in the project file. \n\nThe current order in the `.fsproj` is:\n1. Services.fs\n2. Domain.fs\n3. Program.fs\n\nBut `Services.fs` depends on `Domain.fs` (it opens `BrokenOrder.Domain`), so `Domain.fs` must come before `Services.fs`. And `Program.fs` depends on both, so it should be last.\n\nThe correct order should be:\n1. Domain.fs\n2. Services.fs\n\n\n3. Program.fs","outputTokens":431,"requestId":"F031:12D387:25C57EB:29CCC97:69F93E97"},"id":"7f048158-6008-4816-b34e-dd803d7d3a28","timestamp":"2026-05-05T00:49:34.555Z","parentId":"bca239a4-6c64-4f29-a929-158af2f74f46"}
